<h2>Mechanics Pulled From the Best Sonic Games</h2>

What makes Sonic Rush Rerun stand out among Rush fan projects is how it cherry-picks mechanics from across the handheld Sonic library:

<ul>
<li><strong>Boost System:</strong> The classic Rush boost gauge with a speed meter inspired by Sonic Unleashed</li>
<li><strong>Stomp &amp; Air Boost:</strong> Imported from Sonic Colors DS, adding vertical attack options</li>
<li><strong>Wall Jump:</strong> A new addition — hold up on the stick to climb walls</li>
<li><strong>Trick System:</strong> Aerial acrobatics that fill your boost gauge, carried over from the original Rush</li>
<li><strong>Advance 2 Launchers:</strong> The propulsion system from Sonic Advance 2, integrated into level design</li>
<li><strong>Red Star Rings:</strong> 5 hidden per level. Collect all 5 to unlock <strong>remix tracks</strong> of each stage's music</li>
<li><strong>Ghost Runner:</strong> Race against your own times in Time Attack mode</li>
</ul>

